com.cyc.session.CycAddress

  • Packages that use CycAddress 
    Package Description
    com.cyc.session
    Interfaces for configuring and managing connections to a Cyc server.

    • Uses of CycAddress in com.cyc.session

      Methods in com.cyc.session that return CycAddress 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      static CycAddress CycAddress.fromAddress(CycAddress address)
      Creates a new CycAddress from an existing CycAddress.
      static CycAddress CycAddress.fromAddress(CycAddress address, Integer concurrencyLevel)
      Creates a new CycAddress from an existing CycAddress, but with a new concurrencyLevel.
      static CycAddress CycAddress.fromAddressWithDefaults(CycAddress address, Integer defaultConcurrencyLevel)
      Creates a new CycAddress from an existing CycAddress, setting the concurrency level if unspecified in the original address.
      static CycAddress CycAddress.fromString(String string)
      Creates a new CycAddress instance from a string matching the format host:port.
      static CycAddress CycAddress.get(String hostName, int basePort)
      Creates a CycAddress for the given hostName and basePort.
      static CycAddress CycAddress.get(String hostName, int basePort, Integer concurrencyLevel)
      Creates a CycAddress for the given hostName, basePort, and concurrencyLevel.
      CycAddress CycSessionConfiguration.getCycAddress()
      Returns the address of the Cyc server to be connected to.
      CycAddress CycServerInfo.getCycAddress()
      Returns the address of the server the Session is actually connected to (or was connected to).
      CycAddress CycAddress.toBaseAddress()
      Returns a CycAddress consisting only of the host name and base port, excluding optional fields like getConcurrencyLevel().
